      "subtasks": [],
      "created": "2012-11-30T00:42:27.908+0000",
      "description": "In MR1 the fair scheduler allowed the queue of a running job to be changed through the web UI.  For feature parity, this should be supported in MR2, but the web UI seems an inappropriate place to put it because of complicated security implications and lack of programmatic access.  A command line tool makes more sense.\n \nA generic mechanism could be leveraged by other schedulers to support similar types of functionality and would allow us to avoid making changes to all the plumbing each time functionality is added.  Other possible uses might include suspending pools or fetching scheduler-specific information.\n \nThis functionality could be made available through an RPC server within each scheduler, but that would require reserving another port, and would introduce unnecessary confusion if different schedulers implemented the same mechanism in a different way.\n\nA client should be able to send an RPC with a set of key/value pairs, which would be passed to the scheduler.  The RPC would return a string (or set of key/value pairs).",
      "priority": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/priority/3",
        "iconUrl": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg",
        "name": "Major",
        "id": "3"
      },
      "resolution": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/resolution/2",
        "id": "2",
        "description": "The problem described is an issue which will never be fixed.",
        "name": "Won't Fix"
