              "displayName": "Sandy Ryza",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "My original thinking was that this would be useful for allowing applications to be moved between Fair Scheduler queues from the command line. But my current thinking on that capability is that it would probably be useful to have for all schedulers.  I thought other use cases would come up, but nothing has jumped out at me recently.\n\nIf there are other things a mechanism like this would be useful for, I'm certainly not against adding it.",
